%U A394804 4,6,9,9,0,5,3,9,4,6,0,4,1,9,6,6,8,1,7,4,5,6,9,6,1,3,5,4,6,2,2,0,5,2,7,0,4
%N A394804 Decimal expansion of (4*log(2)-1)/(6*log(2)^2).
%C A394804 The dimensionless coefficient in the expression for the repulsive electrostatic force between two identical charged conducting spheres in contact. If the charge of each sphere is Q and its radius is R, then the force equals c * k * Q^2/(2*R)^2, where k is the Coulomb constant (A182999) and c is this constant. This formula was first published by Lord Kelvin in 1853.
%H A394804 Shubho Banerjee, Mason Levy, McKenna Davis, and Blake Wilkerson, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1109/TIA.2017.2672744">Exact and approximate capacitance and force expressions for the electrostatic interaction between two equal-sized charged conducting spheres</a>, IEEE Transactions on Industry Applications, Vol. 53, No. 3 (2017), pp. 2455-2460; <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Mckenna-Breddan/publication/314251262">ResearchGate link</a>. See p. 2459.
%H A394804 Aditya S. Khair, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1063/1.4824540">Electrostatic forces on two almost touching nonspherical charged conductors</a>, Journal of Applied Physics, Vol. 114, No. 13 (2013), Article 134906. See eq. (1).
%H A394804 Francesco Lacava, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-05099-2">Classical Electrodynamics: From Image Charges to the Photon Mass and Magnetic Monopoles</a>, 2nd ed., Springer Cham, 2022. See pp. 89, 94-96.
%H A394804 John Lekner, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1098/rspa.2012.0133">Electrostatics of two charged conducting spheres</a>, Proceedings of the Royal Society A: Mathematical, Physical and Engineering Sciences, Vol. 468, No. 2145 (2012), 2829-2848; <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/258710075">ResearchGate link</a>. See eq. (1.1), p. 2829.
%H A394804 John Lekner, <a href="https://doi.org/10.13128/substantia-33">Nurturing genius: the childhood and youth of Kelvin and Maxwell</a>, New Zealand Science Review, Vol. 69, No. 1 (2012), pp. 8-14.
%H A394804 John Lekner, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1119/1.4942449">Regions of attraction between like-charged conducting spheres</a>, American Journal of Physics, Vol. 84, No. 6 (2016), pp. 474-477. See eq. (20), p. 476.
%H A394804 John Lekner, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1063/9780735423350">Electrostatics of Conducting Cylinders and Spheres</a>, AIP Publishing LLC, 2021. See section 4.6, pp. 4-11 - 4-15.
%H A394804 Francesco Maccarrone and Giampiero Paffuti, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.elstat.2016.11.001">Some comments on the electrostatic forces between circular electrodes</a>, Journal of Electrostatics, Vol. 84 (2016), pp. 135-142. See eq. (1), p. 135.
%H A394804 William Thomson (Lord Kelvin), <a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/14786445308647247">On the mutual attraction or repulsion between two electrified spherical conductors</a>, The London, Edinburgh, and Dublin Philosophical Magazine and Journal of Science, Series 4, Vol. 5, No. 32 (1853), pp. 287-297. Also published in: William Thomson, <a href="https://archive.org/details/reprintofpaperso00kelv/page/86/mode/2up">Reprint of papers on electrostatics and magnetism</a>, London: Macmillan & Co., 1884, pp. 86-97.
